9
00:00:36,007 --> 00:00:38,043
Non-fat mocha, please.

10
00:00:42,327 --> 00:00:43,601
What?

11
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:46,042
As flattered as we are that
you've chosen our company over,

12
00:00:46,207 --> 00:00:47,765
oh, say, a shower...

13
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:51,606
...perhaps you'd like to go to the
ladies' room to freshen up a bit?

14
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:54,440
Hey, at least I try
to keep in shape.

15
00:00:54,607 --> 00:00:56,837
I haven't seen either one of you
run an eight-minute mile.

16
00:00:57,007 --> 00:00:58,998
Stand upwind of us and you might.

17
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:04,765
Oh, by the way, Niles, my benefit
for the Seattle Theatre Ensemble

18
00:01:04,927 --> 00:01:06,679
is tonight. I haven't
received your check yet.

19
00:01:06,847 --> 00:01:08,678
That's because I'm still
not sure if I'm coming.

20
00:01:08,847 --> 00:01:10,963
Whom should I expect
to meet there?

21
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:13,801
Professional people
around our age.

22
00:01:14,527 --> 00:01:16,358
- A certain social standing.
- Yes.

23
00:01:16,527 --> 00:01:18,085
Civic-minded,
interested in the arts...

24
00:01:18,247 --> 00:01:19,965
Oh, for God's sake,
how many women?

25
00:01:20,127 --> 00:01:21,162
Why didn't you just say so?

26
00:01:21,327 --> 00:01:23,124
Well, I thought my
rutting-monkey body language

27
00:01:23,287 --> 00:01:24,879
would have tipped you off.

28
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:27,520
Well, judging from my RSVP list,

29
00:01:27,687 --> 00:01:29,405
there should be quite
